Name: Swagger Petstore - OpenAPI 3.0
Description:
This is a sample Pet Store Server based on the OpenAPI 3.0 specification.  You can find out more about
Swagger at [https://swagger.io](https://swagger.io). In the third iteration of the pet store, we've switched to the design first approach!
You can now help us improve the API whether it's by making changes to the definition itself or to the code.
That way, with time, we can improve the API in general, and expose some of the new features in OAS3.

Some useful links:
- [The Pet Store repository](https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-petstore)
- [The source API definition for the Pet Store](https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-petstore/blob/master/src/main/resources/openapi.yaml)

Endpoints.Name: updatePet
Endpoints.Description: Update an existing pet by Id.

Endpoints.Name: addPet
Endpoints.Description: Add a new pet to the store.
Endpoints.Summary: Add a new pet to the store.

Endpoints.Name: findPetsByStatus
Endpoints.Description: Multiple status values can be provided with comma separated strings.

Parameters.Name: status
Parameters.Description: Status values that need to be considered for filter

Endpoints.Name: findPetsByTags
Endpoints.Description: Multiple tags can be provided with comma separated strings. Use tag1, tag2, tag3 for testing.

Endpoints.Name: updatePetWithForm
Endpoints.Description: Updates a pet resource based on the form data.
Endpoints.Summary: Updates a pet in the store with form data.

Parameters.Name: petId
Parameters.Description: ID of pet that needs to be updated

Parameters.Name: name
Parameters.Description: Name of pet that needs to be updated

Parameters.Name: status
Parameters.Description: Status of pet that needs to be updated

Endpoints.Name: getInventory
Endpoints.Description: Returns a map of status codes to quantities.

Endpoints.Name: placeOrder
Endpoints.Description: Place a new order in the store.
Endpoints.Summary: Place an order for a pet.

Endpoints.Name: getOrderById
Endpoints.Description: For valid response try integer IDs with value <= 5 or > 10. Other values will generate exceptions.

Parameters.Name: orderId
Parameters.Description: ID of order that needs to be fetched

Endpoints.Name: deleteOrder
Endpoints.Description: For valid response try integer IDs with value < 1000. Anything above 1000 or non-integers will generate API errors.

Parameters.Name: orderId
Parameters.Description: ID of the order that needs to be deleted

Endpoints.Name: createUser
Endpoints.Description: This can only be done by the logged in user.

Endpoints.Name: createUsersWithListInput
Endpoints.Description: Creates list of users with given input array.
Endpoints.Summary: Creates list of users with given input array.

Headers.Name: X-Rate-Limit
Headers.Description: calls per hour allowed by the user

Headers.Name: X-Expires-After
Headers.Description: date in UTC when token expires

ResponseHeaders.Name: X-Rate-Limit
ResponseHeaders.Description: calls per hour allowed by the user

ResponseHeaders.Name: X-Expires-After
ResponseHeaders.Description: date in UTC when token expires

Parameters.Name: password
Parameters.Description: The password for login in clear text

Endpoints.Name: logoutUser
Endpoints.Description: Log user out of the system.
Endpoints.Summary: Logs out current logged in user session.
